RIYADH: Saudi energy minister Prince Abdulaziz bin Salman bin Abdulaziz held a meeting with the Bahraini Minister of Sustainable Development Noor bint Ali Al-Khalif in Riyadh on Thursday, Saudi Press Agency reported. The two sides discussed opportunities and areas of cooperation between the two countries in implementing the circular carbon economy approach, as well as ways to best achieve sustainable development. They also spoke about the Saudi Green and Green Middle East initiatives, and ways both countries can support them. the achievement of , the common interests of the two countries, and the aspirations of their two brotherly leaderships and peoples.